<number box="[1213,1221,400,414]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1230,1237,400,414]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="5.0">5</number>
. Costal setula on wing apex bent 
<quantity box="[329,446,423,447]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="0.165">0.165 mm</quantity>
. M 
<number box="[481,488,438,452]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="3.0">3</number>
+ 
<number box="[497,505,438,452]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="4.0">4</number>
only slightly recurved sub-basally. Halter dark brown, stalk ochreous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,883]" box="[197,654,462,486]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis box="[197,250,463,486]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Legs</emphasis>
yellow, femoral apices light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,883]" box="[197,1386,498,522]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis box="[197,303,498,522]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Dark brown with sternites paler. Ventral components of the postabdomen entirely membranous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,883]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis box="[197,360,534,558]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Subepandrial sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[625,706,534,558]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 47" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1575,1598]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,181,1553]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,159,1598]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 47. Poecilovitila brevicornis sp. n., male genitalia. 41 = subepandrial sclerite with contours of epandrium and surstyli, anterior subventral view, 42 = surstylus, broadest inner (medial) view, 43 = hypandrium, basiphallus and phallapodeme, dorsal view (pre- and postgonites omitted, the pair of connecting sclerites to pregonites dashed), 44 = pregonite with hypandrium, lateral view, 45 = postgonite, caudal view, 46 = same, true lateral view, 47 = ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Scales: 0.2 mm for Fig. 41, 0.1 mm for Figs 42 – 47." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[677,706,534,558]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
) rather small. Surstylus (
<figureCitation box="[987,1068,534,558]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 47" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1575,1598]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,181,1553]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,159,1598]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 47. Poecilovitila brevicornis sp. n., male genitalia. 41 = subepandrial sclerite with contours of epandrium and surstyli, anterior subventral view, 42 = surstylus, broadest inner (medial) view, 43 = hypandrium, basiphallus and phallapodeme, dorsal view (pre- and postgonites omitted, the pair of connecting sclerites to pregonites dashed), 44 = pregonite with hypandrium, lateral view, 45 = postgonite, caudal view, 46 = same, true lateral view, 47 = ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Scales: 0.2 mm for Fig. 41, 0.1 mm for Figs 42 – 47." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[1039,1068,534,558]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
) short boat-shaped, with a group of longer, rounder apical pegs, and with 
<number box="[599,613,570,594]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="8.0">8</number>
blunt pegs on the inner surface of its medial edge. Pregonite (
<figureCitation box="[1302,1383,570,594]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 47" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1575,1598]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,181,1553]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,159,1598]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 47. Poecilovitila brevicornis sp. n., male genitalia. 41 = subepandrial sclerite with contours of epandrium and surstyli, anterior subventral view, 42 = surstylus, broadest inner (medial) view, 43 = hypandrium, basiphallus and phallapodeme, dorsal view (pre- and postgonites omitted, the pair of connecting sclerites to pregonites dashed), 44 = pregonite with hypandrium, lateral view, 45 = postgonite, caudal view, 46 = same, true lateral view, 47 = ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Scales: 0.2 mm for Fig. 41, 0.1 mm for Figs 42 – 47." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[1353,1383,570,594]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="44.0">44</number>
</figureCitation>
) relatively large, particularly compared to hypandrium, which is short and robust (
<figureCitation box="[1041,1173,606,630]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 47" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1575,1598]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,181,1553]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,159,1598]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 47. Poecilovitila brevicornis sp. n., male genitalia. 41 = subepandrial sclerite with contours of epandrium and surstyli, anterior subventral view, 42 = surstylus, broadest inner (medial) view, 43 = hypandrium, basiphallus and phallapodeme, dorsal view (pre- and postgonites omitted, the pair of connecting sclerites to pregonites dashed), 44 = pregonite with hypandrium, lateral view, 45 = postgonite, caudal view, 46 = same, true lateral view, 47 = ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Scales: 0.2 mm for Fig. 41, 0.1 mm for Figs 42 – 47." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Figs 
<number box="[1099,1173,606,630]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="43.5" valueMax="44.0" valueMin="43.0">43–44</number>
</figureCitation>
). Postgonite 
<number box="[1319,1333,606,630]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 47" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1575,1598]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,181,1553]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,159,1598]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 47. Poecilovitila brevicornis sp. n., male genitalia. 41 = subepandrial sclerite with contours of epandrium and surstyli, anterior subventral view, 42 = surstylus, broadest inner (medial) view, 43 = hypandrium, basiphallus and phallapodeme, dorsal view (pre- and postgonites omitted, the pair of connecting sclerites to pregonites dashed), 44 = pregonite with hypandrium, lateral view, 45 = postgonite, caudal view, 46 = same, true lateral view, 47 = ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Scales: 0.2 mm for Fig. 41, 0.1 mm for Figs 42 – 47." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="45.5" valueMax="46.0" valueMin="45.0">45– 46</number>
</figureCitation>
) with rather intricate apical part: rather broad in true lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[950,1036,642,666]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 47" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1575,1598]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,181,1553]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,159,1598]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 47. Poecilovitila brevicornis sp. n., male genitalia. 41 = subepandrial sclerite with contours of epandrium and surstyli, anterior subventral view, 42 = surstylus, broadest inner (medial) view, 43 = hypandrium, basiphallus and phallapodeme, dorsal view (pre- and postgonites omitted, the pair of connecting sclerites to pregonites dashed), 44 = pregonite with hypandrium, lateral view, 45 = postgonite, caudal view, 46 = same, true lateral view, 47 = ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Scales: 0.2 mm for Fig. 41, 0.1 mm for Figs 42 – 47." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[1005,1036,642,666]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="46.0">46</number>
</figureCitation>
), actually with a subapical process (
<figureCitation box="[159,246,678,702]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 47" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1575,1598]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,181,1553]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,159,1598]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 47. Poecilovitila brevicornis sp. n., male genitalia. 41 = subepandrial sclerite with contours of epandrium and surstyli, anterior subventral view, 42 = surstylus, broadest inner (medial) view, 43 = hypandrium, basiphallus and phallapodeme, dorsal view (pre- and postgonites omitted, the pair of connecting sclerites to pregonites dashed), 44 = pregonite with hypandrium, lateral view, 45 = postgonite, caudal view, 46 = same, true lateral view, 47 = ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Scales: 0.2 mm for Fig. 41, 0.1 mm for Figs 42 – 47." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,246,678,702]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="45.0">45</number>
</figureCitation>
). Left ribbon of the mesophallus with dense medium-long setae. Phallapodeme (
<figureCitation box="[1174,1258,678,702]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 47" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1575,1598]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,181,1553]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,159,1598]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 47. Poecilovitila brevicornis sp. n., male genitalia. 41 = subepandrial sclerite with contours of epandrium and surstyli, anterior subventral view, 42 = surstylus, broadest inner (medial) view, 43 = hypandrium, basiphallus and phallapodeme, dorsal view (pre- and postgonites omitted, the pair of connecting sclerites to pregonites dashed), 44 = pregonite with hypandrium, lateral view, 45 = postgonite, caudal view, 46 = same, true lateral view, 47 = ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Scales: 0.2 mm for Fig. 41, 0.1 mm for Figs 42 – 47." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[1229,1258,678,702]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
) very short but fused strongly to hypandrium, pregonite and basiphallus (the pair of connecting sclerites to pregonites stressed on that figure). Ejaculatory apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[543,624,750,774]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 47" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1575,1598]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,181,1553]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,159,1598]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 47. Poecilovitila brevicornis sp. n., male genitalia. 41 = subepandrial sclerite with contours of epandrium and surstyli, anterior subventral view, 42 = surstylus, broadest inner (medial) view, 43 = hypandrium, basiphallus and phallapodeme, dorsal view (pre- and postgonites omitted, the pair of connecting sclerites to pregonites dashed), 44 = pregonite with hypandrium, lateral view, 45 = postgonite, caudal view, 46 = same, true lateral view, 47 = ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Scales: 0.2 mm for Fig. 41, 0.1 mm for Figs 42 – 47." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[595,624,750,774]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="47.0">47</number>
</figureCitation>
) with rather membranous rod, its curvature in lateral view is in all probability a consequence of the hydroxide maceration of the genitalia of a somewhat teneral male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,883]" box="[197,817,822,846]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis box="[197,281,822,846]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Female</emphasis>
postfrons yellowish brown, prefrons yellowish.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1243,858,883]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,883]" box="[197,1243,858,883]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,332,859,883]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet of this new species refers to its comparatively short antenna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
